race.comment: IDLEONBY (8) impressed in his first preparation and returns today, owning two wins at the Flemington jumpouts. She maps for the run of the race and has plenty of upside. Tough to roll. SCREAM (5) peaks off a tidy placing at Mornington in a 62. Carries more weight but has genuine claims on a 9-day back-up. LEGACY BEL (10) has jumped out since a plainer effort last time and Wangaratta, though her form prior was very strong. Drops back to the short course today and if she can bounce back to her prior form. BLEAK MID WINTER (2) lands here first-up with two jumpouts under his belt for the new trainer. Was very impressive when resuming last campaign before being tried in metropolitan company. Keep safe.
